\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Notice that tablature beam segments are thinner and are set farther apart than ordinary beams.  \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\b To make a tablature chord\b0  \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The Tools palette includes tablature tools as shown above.  These provide default tablature chords with durations ranging from whole note to 32nd note, but of course many more options are available by using the Tablature Inspector.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Select a tool.  Click on a staff to place the tablature chord where the pointer is.  Tablature chords are designed to be placed on tablature staves (see \b System\b0 ), because tablature staves have slightly wider spaces to accommodate the note symbols. \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Where on the tablature chord the mouse clicks when a it is selected is significant.  If a tablature chord is clicked where a note symbol can appear, that area will be surrounded by brackets.  A keypress will cause an appropriate note symbol to be displayed at that place.  For numeric note symbols use the digit keys; for alphabetic note symbols use the letter keys.  To erase the note symbol at that place, use the space key.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 When the entry point is where a diapason normally appears, the slash character `/' may be typed to increase the diapason number (type repeatedly until the desired diapason is shown), and a letter (or digit) may be typed to indicate a fret position.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 A keypress outside the area of the note symbols (\i i.e\i0 . on the duration indicator) will allow keypresses to be treated as verse underlay input.  \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\b To alter the tablature placement\b0  \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb0\sa240\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Select the tablature chord and hold the mouse button down to drag the tablature chord to a desired location.  A  tablature chord attaches itself to the nearest staff.  While a tablature chord is being dragged between staves, only its duration flag is shown.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\b The Tablature Inspector\b0   \par
