\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\f1\fs24\b0 S\f1 how\f0\f0\fs24  \f1\f1\fs24 T\f1 ime\f0\f0\fs24 :\f0  If the flag button is selected, a time indicator will be displayed above the column of note symbols.  If the blank button is selected, the time indicator is not shown, and Calliope assumes that the time is that of the previous tablature chord on the staff, in accordance with conventional usage.  The duration of the tablature chord is specified with the note value and dot buttons.  The note value and dot may also be modified by keyboard equivalents.\f0 \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\f1\fs24\b0 B\f1 ody\f0\f0\fs24 :\f0   Specifies the style of the time indicator.\f0 \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\f1\fs24\b0 C\f1 ipher\f0\f0\fs24 :\f0   Specifies whether letters or numbers are used to represent note symbols.\f0 \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\f1\fs24\b0 T\f1 ypeface\f0\f0\fs24 :\f0   Specifies whether the Preferences font or the old book font is used to represent note symbols.  The Preferences font (the uppser choice) is \f0 \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\f1\fs24\b0 P\f1 lace\f0\f0\fs24 :\f0   Specifies whether note symbols are placed on a space or line of the staff.\f0 \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\f1\fs24\b0 S\f1 trum\f0\f0\fs24 :\f0   If checked, the tablature chord is replaced by a strum symbol.  The buttons specify a strum down or strum up symbol.  \f0 \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\f1\b0\fs24 S\f1 hortcut\f0\f0 :\f0  Pressing either button will rest the inspector to display the characteristic attributes of common styles.  Certain attributes (\f1\f1\b0 t\f1 ypeface\f0\f0  \f0 and \f1\f1\b0 p\f1 lace\f0\f0 )\f0  are not changed by \f1\f1\b0\i0 S\f1 hortcut\f0\f0 .\f0 \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\f1\fs24\b0 R\f1 eading\f0\f0\fs24 :\f0   Specifies the reading direction of the tablature.  The down-arrow indicates the "top down" reading, where the top position of the staff refers to the first course of the instrument.  The up-arrow indicates the "bottom up" reading, where the bottom position of the staff refers to the first course of the instument.  \f0 \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\f1\fs24\b0 T\f1 uning\f0\f0\fs24 :\f0   Specifies the instrument that will perform this tablature during playback (see Playback).  Among the choices of instrument are Lute in G, Theorbo in A, Cittern, Bandora.  Using the Instrumentation Inspector (see \b Instrumentation\f0\b0\f0\fs24 )\f0 , new instruments can be defined and instrument can be retuned to any tuning.\f0 \par
